{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id792b846c-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s694–2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"694–2"},"text":"§ 694–2.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Revolving fund for qualified contract guarantees; investment of idle funds","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"There is created within the Treasury a separate fund for guarantees which shall be available to the Administrator without fiscal year limitations as a revolving fund for the purpose of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s694–1"},"text":"section 694–1 of this title","children":[],"tail":". All amounts received by the Administrator, including any moneys, property, or assets derived by him from his operations in connection with "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s694–1"},"text":"section 694–1 of this title","children":[],"tail":" shall be deposited in the fund. All expenses and payments, excluding administrative expenses, pursuant to operations of the Administrator under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s694–1"},"text":"section 694–1 of this title","children":[],"tail":" shall be paid from the fund. Moneys in the fund not needed for the payment of current operating expenses or for the payment of claims arising under this part may be invested in bonds or other obligations of, or bonds or other obligations guaranteed as to principal and interest by, the United States; except that moneys provided as capital for the fund shall not be so invested."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id792b846d-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/699/tIV/s405"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–699, title IV, § 405","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/305/tI/s102"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–305, title I, § 102","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-06-04"},"text":"June 4, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/665"},"text":"90 Stat. 665","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/89/tI/s104"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–89, title I, § 104","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1977-08-04"},"text":"Aug. 4, 1977","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/91/556"},"text":"91 Stat. 556","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/302/tI/s112"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–302, title I, § 112","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-07-02"},"text":"July 2, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/837"},"text":"94 Stat. 837","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id792b846e-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id792b846f-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id792b8470-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1980—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/302"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–302","children":[],"tail":" inserted investment of idle funds provision."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1977—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/89"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–89","children":[],"tail":" prohibited payment of administrative expenses from the fund and deleted provisions which authorized: a $15,000,000 appropriation of capital for the fund; payment during the fiscal year into the Treasury as miscellaneous receipts, from the fund, of interest on the cumulative amount of appropriations available as capital to the fund less the average undisbursed cash balance in the fund during the year; and investment of noncapital moneys, when not needed for payment of current operating expenses or claims arising under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s694–2"},"text":"section 694–2 of this title","children":[],"tail":", in Federal bonds or obligations or bonds or obligations guaranteed by the United States as to principal and interest."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id792b8471-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id792b8472-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1980 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/302"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–302","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 1980","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/302/s507"},"text":"section 507 of Pub. L. 96–302","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s631"},"text":"section 631 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id792b8473-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1977 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"r